HEADWORD: Sauerkraut
<hw>Sauer"kraut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr.
<ets>sauer</ets> sour + <ets>kraut</ets> herb, cabbage.]</ety>
<def>Cabbage cut fine and allowed to ferment in a brine made of its own
juice with salt, -- a German dish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

